import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['index'] = pd.to_datetime(data['index'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', label=f'mean={data["u"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['index'] = pd.to_datetime(data['index'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='index', y='u', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['u'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the trend of u over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
